initial statement:
 1190
Your Honor,

I stand before this court today to plead guilty to the charge of assault. I fully acknowledge my wrongdoing and take full responsibility for my actions.

I deeply regret the events that transpired on that day. It was an unfortunate incident where I pushed my employee to the ground and proceeded to kick him in the stomach. I must clarify that this act was an isolated incident and is not indicative of my character or conduct in general.

I want to provide some context to the court regarding my actions. My employee had made a grave mistake that would have had severe financial implications for my company. This unfortunate circumstance filled me with intense anger and frustration. In that moment, I lost control of my emotions and reacted in a way that I deeply regret.

Immediately after the incident, I recognized the gravity of my actions and took swift measures to ensure the well-being of the victim. I promptly brought him to the closest emergency room to receive appropriate medical attention. I am relieved to report that he is now in a stable condition. I have made a sincere apology to the victim and his family, expressing my remorse for the pain and distress I caused them.

In addition to my heartfelt apology, I have taken it upon myself to make amends for the harm caused. I have voluntarily offered to cover the victim's remaining medical expenses, as a testament to my commitment to his recovery and to demonstrate my genuine remorse.

Your Honor, I would like to highlight that I have led a law-abiding life up until this incident. I have no prior criminal record, which attests to the fact that this act is an anomaly and not indicative of my character.

As a 40-year-old individual, I understand that I am not absolved of the consequences of my actions. Nevertheless, I respectfully request the court's consideration of the mitigating factors in this case. My guilty plea demonstrates my acceptance of responsibility, showcasing my willingness to face the consequences of my actions and to learn from this experience.

I assure the court that I have taken significant steps to prevent a recurrence of such behavior. Through counseling and therapy, I have begun addressing the underlying issues that led to my loss of self-control in that moment. I am fully committed to my rehabilitation and to becoming a better person.

Finally, I would like to express the emotional toll that this incident has taken on me. The remorse and regret I feel are profound, and I am determined to make amends and contribute positively to society. I sincerely hope that through my actions moving forward, I can demonstrate my commitment to personal growth and to making restitution for the pain I have caused.

Your Honor, I humbly request leniency from this court and ask for the opportunity to demonstrate through my actions that I am genuinely remorseful and capable of change.
